EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to legislative affairs; revising provisions relating
to requests for the drafting of legislative measures; and
providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law establishes the number and timing of requests for the drafting of
2 legislative measures for Legislators and for other requesters. (NRS
3 218D.150-218D.220)
4 Existing law authorizes incumbent members of the Assembly to request, before
5 a regular session, the drafting of up to 9 legislative measures and incumbent
6 Senators to request the drafting of up to 18 legislative measures, with portions of
7 these requests due to the Legislative Counsel by August 1 preceding session and
8 December 10 preceding session. (NRS 218D.150) Section 1 of this bill: (1) reduces
9 the total number of authorized pre-session requests from 9 to 6 for members of the
10 Assembly and from 18 to 12 for Senators; (2) divides this number of pre-session
11 requests equally between the two deadline periods; (3) establishes a deadline for
12 submission of information sufficient in detail to allow for the complete drafting of
13 or a withdrawal of each request for each deadline period; and (4) reduces the
14 number of requests available in subsequent pre-session deadline periods if a
15 Legislator does not submit information sufficient in detail to allow for the complete
16 drafting of or withdraw a request from the previous deadline period.
17 In addition to the requests for the drafting of legislative measures available to
18 Legislators generally, existing law authorizes the Speaker and Minority Leader of
19 the Assembly and the Majority Leader and Minority Leader of the Senate to request
20 the drafting of certain additional legislative measures before a regular session.
21 (NRS 218D.155) Section 2 of this bill reduces the number of requests authorized
22 for the Speaker of the Assembly and Majority Leader of the Senate from 15 to 10
23 and for the Minority Leaders of the Assembly and Senate from 10 to 5.
24 Existing law authorizes the Governor, Lieutenant Governor, Secretary of State,
25 State Treasurer, State Controller and Attorney General to request the drafting of
-
