26 certain numbers of legislative measures before a regular session on or before
27 certain dates and establishes deadlines by which such legislative measures must be
28 prefiled or deemed withdrawn. (NRS 218D.175) Section 3 of this bill revises the
29 deadline for the submission of the request for the drafting of not more than 5
30 legislative measures by the Governor to propose the Governor’s legislative agenda
31 from the 19th day of a regular session to: (1) August 1, if no gubernatorial election
32 will occur before the regular session; or (2) after the first Monday in January and on
33 or before the first day of the regular session, if a gubernatorial election will occur
34 before the regular session.
35 While existing law does not establish a prefiling deadline for legislative
36 measures that propose the Governor’s legislative agenda, Joint Standing Rule No.
37 14.2 of the Senate and Assembly requires all bills to be introduced not later than the
38 50th calendar day of a regular session. Additionally, the Nevada Constitution
39 requires the Governor to submit the proposed executive budget to the Legislature
40 not later than 14 calendar days before the commencement of each regular session.
41 (Nev. Const. Art. 4, § 2) Section 3 establishes deadlines for the legislative
42 measures that propose the Governor’s legislative agenda that require: (1) prefiling
43 such measures on or before the 10th calendar day preceding the regular session if
44 no gubernatorial election will occur before the regular session; or (2) introducing
45 such measures on or before the 15th day of the regular session if a gubernatorial
46 election will occur before the regular session.
47 Finally, section 3 reduces the number of requests for the drafting of legislative
48 measures before a regular session by: (1) the Lieutenant Governor from 3 to 2; (2)
49 the Secretary of State from 8 to 6; (3) the State Treasurer from 5 to 4; (4) the State
50 Controller from 5 to 4; and (5) the Attorney General from 20 to 16.
